race.comment: THE LONGEST YARD (7) was sent out at long odds when resuming but ran above expectations, beaten 1L over 1200m at Launceston. He's improved, and 3x winning rider Jordan is reunited. Fitter and the longer sprint suits. Just has to hold that form to win. LILY LUELLA (8) resumed in the same contest and finished just behind the above after racing forward. Has the winkers on again and is proven second-up. VERBANO (5) won a 72 this trip and then raced over a mile beaten 2L in a 76. Carries more weight at this level, but is a decent chance to bounce. JUST A NEEDS (1) resumes and has been racing in stronger. She's won fresh and has the inside gate. Has the handy 3kg claim and is worth a market watch.
